      "message": "@vedangimittal3004@gmail.com\n\nWhile testing the multi-session flow I hit a data-freshness issue. Steps to reproduce:\n\nLog in from Browser A → 1 session shown (correct).\nLog in from Browser B (same user) → server now has 2 sessions. B shows 2, but A still shows 1 even after a page refresh.\nFrom Browser A, disconnect a session → Browser B keeps showing it, even after refreshing the page.\nRoot cause (likely): useSessions uses useRedfishCollection, which disables all auto-refetch triggers and sets no staleTime:\n\nBecause the cached data is served on remount, a page refresh re-reads the cache and skips the network call, so each browser keeps showing its own stale list.\n\nExpectation: Sessions are mutable, shared state. A page refresh (and ideally window-focus) should reflect the current server state. Live cross-browser sync (instant updates without refresh) would need polling/SSE and is out of scope — but stale-on-refresh should be fixed.\n\nSuggestion: Have useSessions override the query options (e.g. refetchOnMount: true / refetchOnWindowFocus: true with a small staleTime). Please confirm useRedfishCollection forwards query-option overrides; if not, that override path may need to be added.",
